{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id9123fec7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9255"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9255"},"text":"§ 9255.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authority to consolidate reports","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any and all reports required to be submitted to appropriate congressional committees under this chapter or any amendment made by this Act that are subject to a deadline for submission consisting of the same unit of time may be consolidated into a single report that is submitted to appropriate congressional committees pursuant to such deadline. The consolidated reports must contain all information required under this chapter or any amendment made by this Act, in addition to all other elements mandated by previous law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id9123fec8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/122/tIV/s405"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–122, title IV, § 405","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-18"},"text":"Feb. 18, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/116"},"text":"130 Stat. 116","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id9123fec9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id9123feca-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id9123fecb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/122"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–122","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-18"},"text":"Feb. 18, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/93"},"text":"130 Stat. 93","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s9201"},"text":"section 9201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any amendment made by this Act, referred to in text, means the amendments made by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/122"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–122","children":[],"tail":". See Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s9201"},"text":"section 9201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
